Nuclear medicine diagnosis--principles and indications. Diagnostic procedures in nuclear medicine are functional studies of localized processes. The gathered informations are generally different to those acquired by imaging methods such as ultrasound and x-ray. Frequently, both methods are complementary. This review provides survey about the scintigraphic diagnostic procedures of following organs: Endocrine organs, especially the thyroid gland heart, especially myocardial perfusion and viability, functional studies of the kidney, lung ventilation and perfusion, bone, bone marrow and inflammation, brain, gastrointestinal tract diagnostics and tumour scintigraphy.